President Muhammadu Buhari has rejected the Amended Electoral Bill sent for his signature by the National Assembly. The President notified the Senate about his action in a letter to the President of the Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki during plenary on Tuesday. Buhari said the amendment infringed on the INEC right of discretion as provided in Section 15 (a) of the Third Schedule to the Constitution. === The Federal government has intensified efforts to counter acts of terrorism and insurgency in the country. To this end, Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps embarked on counter-terrorism drills to enhance proficiency of personnel in the counter insurgency Operations in the Northeast. ===== Parents of the abducted Dapchi schoolgirls in Yobe have called on President Muhammadu Buhari to deploy all resources at his disposal to rescue the girls. The parents also commended the President for choosing to employ dialogue and negotiation option rather than force in the effort to ensure the safe return of the girls.  American President, Donald Trump has sacked the US Secretary of State, Rex Tillerson. Trump, who announced the sack on his Twitter handle, also announced the appointment of CIA director, Mike Pompeo as the new US Secretary of State. Tillerson just concluded a six-nation tour of Africa, during which he pledged US support in their fight against terrorism. === Investigators have retrieved the flight data recorder from the wreckage of a Bangladeshi airliner that crashed on Monday. At least 49 persons aboard the airline died while it attempted to land in Nepal’s capital. The incident is the nation’s worst since the 1992 crash of a Pakistan International aircraft which killed 167 people.